<HEADLINE>
BC DEFENSE LEFT DEFENSELESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By PAUL HARBER  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Syracuse quarterback Donovan McNabb had a plan going
into Saturday's 42-25 Big East victory over Boston College.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was to spread it around,'' said the Heisman Trophy
candidate. ``Let everybody get in on offense.''
</P>
<P>
   And that's exactly what he did. Statistics don't tell the real
story. Both teams had 20 first downs. Both teams had similar
