<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VAN RAAPHORST SIDELINED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PULLMAN, Wash. _ It's not being called a case of nerves, but USC
quarterback Mike Van Raaphorst left the Washington State game in
the second quarter and returned to the locker room after repeatedly
vomiting.
</P>
<P>
   Van Raaphorst did not return to the field for the start of the
second half.
</P>
<P>
   It is the third time this year Van Raaphorst has experienced
stomach problems. He was up the night before the Purdue game with
an upset stomach and experienced vomiting during warmups against
Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   Although officials said he had food poisoning against Purdue and
stomach flu against Florida State, there have been lingering
suspicions that Van Raaphorst has been bothered by nerves on game
days.
</P>
<P>
   His performance certainly gave little impression that he was
ill. Van Raaphorst was 9 of 15 for 99 yards and a touchdown when he
left the game.
</P>
<P>
   Freshman quarterback Carson Palmer made one of his earliest
appearances of the season when he replaced Van Raaphorst with 6:41
left in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   It was Palmer's second chance to play in the first half. He also
played in the first half against Oregon State.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer threw a 2-yard touchdown pass to Lonnie Ford in the third
quarter that gave USC a 28-14 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer's appearance was earlier than USC coach Paul Hackett
intended. Hackett had said he would keep the quarterback rotation
intact, which meant a third-quarter appearance for Palmer.
</P>
<P>
   Oregon time set: With ABC choosing to televise UCLA-California
next week, USC's game at Oregon on Saturday will begin at 3:30
p.m.and will be televised on the Fox Sports syndicate network,
which means the game will be shown on Channel 9 (KCAL-TV) in
Southern California.
</P>
<P>
   Bowl visitors: Two representatives from the Holiday Bowl
attended the game. The Holiday Bowl gets second choice among
Pacific-10 Conference teams, but could be selecting third if the
Fiesta Bowl were to take UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   Petroff returns: Although he was still a little sore, assistant
coach Larry Petroff made the trip to Pullman. Petroff was
hospitalized this week with kidney stones and missed all practices.
</P>
<P>
   Cusano sits out: Although he suited up, linebacker Mark Cusano
(sore thigh) did not play.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
