<P>
   Oxford English Dictionary.
</P>
<P>
   9. A PIRATE LOOKS AT FIFTY, by Jimmy Buffett. (Random
</P>
<P>
   House, $24.95.) While traveling from the Florida Keys
</P>
<P>
   to the Amazon, the singer-songwriter reflects on his
</P>
<P>
   half-century of life.
</P>
<P>
   10.(x) EAT THE RICH, by P.J. O'Rourke. (Atlantic
</P>
<P>
   Monthly, $24.) The humorist's treatise on economics
</P>
<P>
   and the business world.
</P>
<P>
   11. HIGH CRIMES AND MISDEMEANORS, by Ann H. Coulter.
</P>
<P>
   (Regnery, $24.95.) A lawyer states the case for the
</P>
<P>
   impeachment of President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   12.(x) THE JOY OF WORK, by Scott Adams. (Harper Business,
</P>
<P>
   $22.) In words and cartoons, the creator of ``Dilbert''
</P>
<P>
   suggests ways to become happy by making your co-workers
</P>
<P>
   miserbale.
</P>
<P>
   13.(x) CONVERSATIONS WITH GOD: Book 1, by Neale Donald Walsch.
</P>
<P>
   (Putnam, $19.95.) The author addresses questions
</P>
<P>
   of life and love, good and evil, guilt and sin. (b).
</P>
<P>
   14. A WALK IN THE WOODS, by Bill Bryson. (Broadway, $25.)
</P>
<P>
   A journalist finds beauty and humor while hiking the
</P>
<P>
   Appalachian Trail.
</P>
<P>
   15. WORKING WITH EMOTIONAL INTELLIGENCE, by Daniel Goleman.
</P>
<P>
   (Bantam, $25.95.) The attributes that enable people to become
</P>
<P>
   leaders in their fields.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ADVICE, HOW-TO, AND MISCELLANEOUS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE 9 STEPS TO FINANCIAL FREEDOM, by Suze
</P>
<P>
   Orman. (Crown, $23.) How to manage your money. (b)
</P>
<P>
   2. IF LIFE IS A GAME, THESE ARE THE RULES, by Cherie
</P>
<P>
   Carter-Scott. (Broadway, $15.) Ways to achieve a
</P>
<P>
   fulfilling life. (b)
</P>
<P>
   3. SUGAR BUSTERS, by H. Leighton Steward, et al.
</P>
<P>
   (Ballantine, $22.) A diet designed for losing
</P>
<P>
   weight, increasing energy, and combating disease. (b)
</P>
<P>
   4. IN THE MEANTIME, by Iyanla Vanzant. (Simon &AMP; Schuster,
</P>
<P>
   $23.) Ways to find what you truly need, particularly ``the
</P>
<P>
   love that you want.'' (b)
</P>
