Ashland, Ore. It's just up the street from the All's Well Herb and
Vitamin Shoppe, not far from Puck's Doughnuts and a motel known as
Bard's Inn. Or you could head for the city park where lithia water
_ containing at least 20 minerals _ is offered free of charge. The
city fountains were installed in 1911 in hopes that Ashland might
become a European-style health spa.
