nutritious food that Americans eat at the rate of 8 pounds per
person per year? A symbol for anything petty or insignificant _
``he works for peanuts?'' Not a nut at all, but a legume? A deadly
killer capable of triggering fatal allergic reactions? The answer,
of course, is ``all of the above.'' But it's the deadly killer part
that's been attracting attention lately.
</P>
<P>
   By Gregory Roberts. (Story will move in the ``d'' category.)
