conference featuring Bill Gates and a mid-level IBM executive at a
computer show in 1989 first brought Microsoft to the attention of
federal antitrust enforcers. And in the decade since then, the
company has been the subject of unrelenting investigations, one
after another. The issues have molted as the computer industry
matures. But investigators, first with the FTC and then Justice,
have never stopped. By Joel Brinkley.
